---
import DocsLayout from '../../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Center Mode Plugin">
  <h1>Center Mode</h1>
  <p class="lead">Centers the active slide by applying equal padding on both sides of the slider container and setting <code>overflow: visible</code>, allowing the edges of adjacent slides to peek in from either side.</p>

  <h2>Import</h2>
  <pre><code>import {"{"} centerMode {"}"} from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'</code></pre>

  <h2>Options</h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Option</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>centerPadding</code></td><td><code>string</code></td><td><code>'50px'</code></td><td>CSS length applied as equal left and right padding on the slider container. Any valid CSS length unit is accepted (e.g. <code>'80px'</code>, <code>'10%'</code>).</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Notes</h2>
  <p>The plugin sets <code>paddingLeft</code>, <code>paddingRight</code>, and <code>overflow: visible</code> on the slider container. Wrap the slider in a parent with <code>overflow: hidden</code> if you want to clip content beyond the visible area. All styles are removed on destroy.</p>

  <h2>Example</h2>
  <pre><code>{`import { createSlider } from '@andresclua/sliderkit'
import { centerMode } from '@andresclua/sliderkit-plugins'

createSlider('#my-slider', {
  slidesPerPage: 1,
  plugins: [centerMode({ centerPadding: '80px' })],
})`}</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
